Quote:  Sometimes the snow-white downy fibres from the under side of the leaves of the Kowharawhara, and the Kahakaha, (<i>Astelia Cunninghamii</i>, and <i>Solandri</i>,) and the thin transparent epidermis from the leaves of the mountain Tikumu (<i>Celmisia coriacea</i>), were also used ... to ornament ... the head.
